b'' b'********************************************************************' b'* b'* announcing b'* b'* cosy_pak b'* b'* (a symbolic control systems analysis package) b'* b'* version b'* \t\t b'* (no user fee release) b'* b'* for b'* b'* mathematica version or higher b'* b'********************************************************************' b'' b'== introduction' b'' b'cosy_pak is set of packages and notebooks for classical control and' b'(some) modern (state space) control analysis and design methods. the' b"notebooks in cosy_pak follow a typical `control engineering i' course" b'taught at many universities around the world for the junior/senior' b'level undergraduates. there is no fee to use cosy_pak but certain' b'responsibilities are expected of the user (see copyright notice in the' b'readme file included below). for starters e-mail fax mail (post)' b'the registration form included in the readme file.' b'' b"cosy_pak is available via `anonymous ftp' from" b'' b'mishna.esys.cwru.edu (internet no b'' b'in the /pub directory.' b'' b'p.s.: a typical ftp session in unix is given after the readme file.' b'' b'' b'== future releases' b'' b'if you would like to receive updates and newer versions of' b'cosy_pak please send e-mail/fax/mail to the address' b'below. in addition, your comments and suggestions are' b'appreciated and are invaluable to us. we will do our best' b'to fix any reported bugs. however, we cannot fix those' b'bugs that have not been reported to us and those we do not' b'know of. we would very much appreciate you taking a few' b'minutes to communicate to us via e-mail us mail b'telephone fax. this will help us to release bug-free' b'versions in the future. comments are welcome.' b'' b'n. sreenath' b'systems engineering department' b'case school of engineering' b'case western reserve university' b'' b'******************' b'' b'u.s. mail:' b'' b'prof. n. sreenath tel.: b'systems engg., crawford hall fax: b'case western reserve univ.' b'cleveland oh b'' 